gomodel:SYNGO_3037  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Expression pattern of Kcnab2 transcripts encoding for the Kvβ2 protein in the developing CNS\"\n- \"On ultrastructural level Kvβ2 is located at postsynaptic sites in the PSD, visualized by pre-embedded immuno-electron microscopy (Fig. 1G). In subfractions of rat brain protein lysate Kvβ2 is present in all fractions except mitochondria and is enriched in the postsynaptic density. \"\n\nFig.2: \"ProSAP2/Shank3 interacts with Kvβ2 via its PDZ/PRR domain\"\n\nFig.3: \"Kvβ2 is interacting with the PDZ/PRR motifs of ProSAP2/Shank3 and is recruited into the clusters of ProSAP2/Shank3\"\n\n28/3/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Cell culture experiments of rat hippocampal primary neurons...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3037" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

